review.body: For whatever it's worth: This is what I'd call "macro kung-fu" and it looks good to me (certainly the build-and-switch logic as far as I can judge it from reading through it). The other thing I'd do is run comparative performance tests with/without this patch (and obviously with/without AVX2+PORTABLE set) -- but then again, we've got automation for that so maybe we can leave that to after the merge assuming you already did a quick check -- and didn't see a significant regression for algorithms using SHA3 (and AVX2&&PORTABLE active)? Otherwise, please let me know so I'd trigger a profiling run against this branch to check this out before merge.
